						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone built into the raised platform of the dargā outside the village.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tribhuvanamalla (Vikramāditya VI)—A.D. 1085.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 10, Krōdhana, Paushya, śu. 5, Monday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkramaṇa</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1085, December 24.</hi> The weekday was, however, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>The inscription, which consists of two fragments, seems to record the renewal of an earlier gift for a water-shed, students, etc., which had lapsed, by Mahāmaṇḍaḷēśvara <hi rend="bold">Kaliyammarasa,</hi> with the consent of the king who is stated to have been ruling from his capital <hi rend="bold">Kalyāṇa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
